Step one: install hugo

> brew install hugo

Step two: start hugo

> hugo server -D

this will compile and render the files. Any updates are reflected automatically

Step three: create content

Go to content/posts and create a new .md file. Look the existing ones for ideas.

Step four: publish

Kill the server and do a 

> hugo -D 

This generates the public file in /docs

Then, commit -a -m and push the master branch.

Go here https://agentrisk.github.io/overlay-blog/ to check if everything is ok
